{"questionId":"9072713","questionHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:left;\">A solid cylinder of height <em>h</em> and density <em>ρ</em> rests on a flat surface.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/caf775636ecd871086ab1e1483481d69a7c92904.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Show that the pressure <em>p</em><sub>c</sub>&nbsp;exerted by the cylinder on the surface is given by <em>p</em><sub>c</sub>&nbsp;= <em>ρgh</em>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>weight of cylinder =&nbsp;<em>Ahg ρ </em>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>pressure = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{F}{A}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>F</mi>\n    <mi>A</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> = <span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{Ahg\\rho }}{A}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>A</mi>\n      <mi>h</mi>\n      <mi>g</mi>\n      <mi>ρ</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>A</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></span> ✔</p>\n<p><em>Allow use of A =&nbsp;</em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\pi {r^2}\">\n  <mi>π</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></span><em> in MP1</em>.&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9072713","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ1.4a","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A solid cylinder of height h and density ρ rests on a flat surface. Show that the pressure pc exerted by the cylinder on the surface is given by pc = ρgh.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics","3.2 – Modelling a gas","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}